text:
"In August was the Jackal born;
        The Rains fell in September;
     'Now such a fearful flood as this,'
        Says he, 'I can't remember!'"

"They are too close -- too narrow in the hand for my crop," croaked the
      Adjutant. "They waste not the polish on the cow's horn, as the saying is;
      and, again, who can glean after a Malwai?"

"It is not wise to kill cubs and lahinis," Mowgli went on philosophically,
      wiping the blood out of his eyes, "unless one has also killed the Outlier;
      and it is in my stomach that this Won-tolla kills thee."
